ath sale price from the 2.5-bath sale price.", "input_label": "Your Price Difference", "input_suffix": "", "rows": [{"label": "1", "cells": ["$244,000", "$250,200"]}, {"label": "2", "cells": ["$248,500", "$254,800"]}], "column_headers": ["Pair", "2 Full Bath Sale", "2.5 Bath Sale"], "concluded_label": "Concluded Bathroom Adjustment", "concluded_helper": "Bracket your two results."}]}, {"key": "cost", "label": "Cost-Based Support", "intro": "Calculate the depreciated contributory value for both adjustment types. Both cost indications fall BELOW the paired sales range — cost acts as a floor, not a ceiling. The market is paying slightly above depreciated replacement cost for this 2000 vintage. VA guidelines require the appraiser to explain this relationship clearly in the addendum.", "items": [{"kind": "cost_calc", "feature_key": "gla", "title": "GLA Contributory Value ($/SF)", "fact_rows": [["RCN", "$74.00 / SF"], ["Effective Age", "24 years"], ["Economic Life", "60 years"], ["Depreciation Rate", "24 ÷ 60 = 40%"], ["Formula", "$74.00 × (1 − 0.40) = ?"]], "input_suffix": "/SF"}, {"kind": "cost_calc", "feature_key": "bath", "title": "Bathroom Cost (Half-Bath Addition)", "fact_rows": [["Cost to Add Half Bath", "$10,000"], ["Effective Age", "24 years"], ["Economic Life", "60 years"], ["Depreciation Rate", "40%"], ["Formula", "$10,000 × (1 − 0.40) = ?"]], "input_suffix": ""}]}], "reconciliation": {"instruction": "Review both method indications and enter your reconciled adjustment for each item. Both cost indications fall below paired sales — cost is a floor here. Weight the paired sales evidence and explain the cost-as-floor relationship in your VA rationale.", "items": [{"feature_key": "gla", "label": "GLA Adjustment ($/SF)"}, {"feature_key": "bath", "label": "Bathroom Adjustment ($)"}]}}, "step3": {"instruction": "Apply your reconciled adjustments to each comparable. Use a NEGATIVE value where the comp is superior to the subject, and a POSITIVE value where it is inferior. Comps 1 and 3 both require GLA adjustments but in opposite directions (Comp 1 larger, Comp 3 smaller). VA reviewers expect each rationale to cite the specific market evidence used and address the cost-as-floor relationship.", "applicable": {"C1": ["gla"], "C2": ["bath"], "C3": ["gla"]}, "method_dropdown": ["Paired Sales Analysis", "Grouped Paired Sales", "Cost-Based Support", "Income Differential / GRM", "Regression Analysis", "Appraiser Judgment / Extraction"], "support_min_chars": 15}, "step4": {"show_net_gross_panel": false}}'::jsonb,
