SELECT id, 2,
  'intermediate',
  '1654 Meadowlark Way — FHA 203(b) Purchase Loan Appraisal',
  'You are appraising a home at 1654 Meadowlark Way, Spartanburg SC for an FHA-insured purchase loan under the 203(b) program — the most common FHA loan type. The appraisal is ordered by the lender, but you must be on the FHA Appraiser Roster and the appraisal must comply with HUD Handbook 4000.1. The appraisal is tied to the property via FHA Case No. 381-7842156, valid for 120 days; if the first transaction falls through, a second buyer can use the same case number and appraisal. Contract price is $299,500. The appraiser must confirm the property meets HUD Minimum Property Standards (MPS); for this assignment, MPS have been confirmed.

The subject is a 1,980 SF home built in 2006 with three bedrooms, 2.5 bathrooms, and a 2-car garage, in good condition. Three closed sales are provided. They differ from the subject across three adjustment types: GLA, bathrooms, and market conditions (one comparable sold 8 months ago). Two analytical challenges are introduced at this level. First, the GLA paired sales include a divergent Pair 3 — under HUD 4000.1, outlier exclusion must be documented in the addendum, making it a compliance requirement rather than a stylistic choice. Second, both cost indications exceed paired sales — both acting as ceilings — requiring weighting of paired sales in reconciliation. Identify the differing features, derive market-supported adjustment values, apply them, and reconcile the adjusted prices into your FHA appraised value.'
FROM scenario_categories WHERE code = 'M2-S4-C5';

