F / $367,350", "150 SF", "$7,350"]}, {"label": "4", "cells": ["2,150 SF / $342,000", "2,350 SF / $353,800", "200 SF", "$11,800"]}], "column_headers": ["Pair", "Sale A (SF / Price)", "Sale B (SF / Price)", "SF Diff", "Price Diff"], "concluded_label": "Concluded GLA Adjustment", "concluded_helper": "Bracket Pairs 1–3; exclude Pair 4 with documented reasoning."}, {"kind": "paired_dollar_diff", "feature_key": "loc", "title": "Location Pairs — Standard vs. Amenitied/Gated", "instruction": "No cost method available for location. Calculate price difference (Amenitied/Gated minus Standard). Pairs 1–3 cluster tightly; Pair 4 diverges modestly.", "input_label": "Your Price Difference", "input_suffix": "", "rows": [{"label": "1", "cells": ["$349,000", "$364,000"]}, {"label": "2", "cells": ["$356,000", "$371,500"]}, {"label": "3", "cells": ["$362,000", "$377,500"]}, {"label": "4", "cells": ["$344,000", "$360,800"]}], "column_headers": ["Pair", "Standard Sale", "Amenitied/Gated Sale"], "concluded_label": "Concluded Location Adjustment", "concluded_helper": "Bracket Pairs 1–3; address Pair 4."}, {"kind": "paired_dollar_diff", "feature_key": "cnd", "title": "Condition Pairs — Good vs. Average", "instruction": "No cost method available. Calculate price difference (Good minus Average). Three pairs cluster very tightly.", "input_label": "Your Price Difference", "input_suffix": "", "rows": [{"label": "1", "cells": ["$352,000", "$364,200"]}, {"label": "2", "cells": ["$345,000", "$357,200"]}, {"label": "3", "cells": ["$358,500", "$370,800"]}], "column_headers": ["Pair", "Average Sale", "Good Sale"], "concluded_label": "Concluded Condition Adjustment", "concluded_helper": "Three pairs — exceptionally tight bracket."}, {"kind": "paired_pct_per_month", "feature_key": "date", "title": "Market Conditions — Resale Pair Analysis", "instruction": "The same properties sold twice. For each pair, calculate the monthly appreciation rate using: (Resale − Original) ÷ Original ÷ Months × 100", "input_label": "Your %/Month", "input_suffix": "%/mo", "rows": [{"label": "A", "cells": ["$355,000", "$367,900", "10"]}, {"label": "B", "cells": ["$348,000", "$360,400", "11"]}, {"label": "C", "cells": ["$362,000", "$374,700", "10"]}], "column_headers": ["Property", "Original Sale Price", "Resale Price", "Months"], "concluded_label": "Concluded Monthly Rate", "concluded_helper": "Bracket your three results."}]}, {"key": "cost", "label": "Cost-Based Support", "intro": "Only GLA has an applicable cost method. The cost indication exceeds the paired sales range — a clear ceiling. In condemnation proceedings, presenting cost support helps demonstrate that the value conclusion is not artificially inflated. Location, Condition, and Market Conditions are market-derived only.", "items": [{"kind": "cost_calc", "feature_key": "gla", "title": "GLA Contributory Value ($/SF)", "fact_rows": [["RCN", "$83.00 / SF"], ["Effective Age", "19 years"], ["Economic Life", "60 years"], ["Depreciation Rate", "19 ÷ 60 = 31.7%"], ["Formula", "$83.00 × (1 − 0.317) = ?"]], "input_suffix": "/SF"}]}], "reconciliation": {"instruction": "Review both method indications and enter your reconciled adjustment for each item. GLA cost is a clear ceiling — weight paired sales. Location, Condition, and Market Conditions reconcile from paired sales only. In condemnation, every reconciled figure may be challenged; each must fall squarely within the range your evidence supports.", "items": [{"feature_key": "gla", "label": "GLA Adjustment ($/SF)"}, {"feature_key": "loc", "label": "Location Adjustment ($)"}, {"feature_key": "cnd", "label": "Condition Adjustment ($)"}, {"feature_key": "date", "label": "Market Conditions Adjustment (%/mo)"}]}}, "step3": {"instruction": "Apply your reconciled adjustments to each comparable. Use NEGATIVE values for superior comps and POSITIVE for inferior. Comp 1 receives two negative adjustments (GLA + Location). Comp 2 receives one positive (Condition). Comp 3 receives three adjustments — GLA (positive, inferior), Location (negative, superior — opposing direction), and Market Conditions (positive). For Comp 3 (market conditions), calculate as: $369,000 × 11 months × your reconciled %/mo ÷ 100. Address the GLA Pair 4 outlier exclusion in the GLA rationale; for Comp 3''s three adjustments, each must be independently justified.", "applicable": {"C1": ["gla", "loc"], "C2": ["cnd"], "C3": ["gla", "loc", "date"]}, "method_dropdown": ["Paired Sales Analysis", "Location Paired Sales Analysis", "Market Conditions (Resale Pairs)", "Cost-Based Support", "Grouped Paired Sales", "Regression Analysis", "Appraiser Judgment / Extraction"], "support_min_chars": 15}, "step4": {"show_net_gross_panel": true}}'::jsonb,
  '{"step1_correct_flags": {"C1": ["gla", "loc"], "C2": ["cnd"], "C3": ["gla", "loc", "date"]}, "step1_rationale": "Comp 1 differs in two superior features: 150 SF larger (GLA) and amenitied/gated location (Location) — both require negative adjustments. Comp 2 differs in only one feature: average condition versus the subject''s good condition (inferior, requires positive adjustment). Comp 3 differs in three features with opposing directions: 150 SF smaller (inferior GLA, positive adjustment), amenitied/gated location (superior Location, negative adjustment), and sold 11 months ago (inferior Date, positive adjustment). Bathrooms, garage, and year built are equivalent across all three comparables.", "step2_tables": {"paired": {"gla": {"pair_answers": [48.0, 48.0, 49.0, 59.0], "concluded_range": [48.0, 49.0], "rationale": "Pairs 1–3 cluster tightly at $48.00–$49.00/SF — strong, consistent market support. Pair 4 produces $59.00/SF and must be excluded with litigation-quality documented reasoning (different submarket, anomalous transaction, or data anomaly). Bracket conclusion in the $48–$49/SF range."}, "loc": {"pair_answers": [15000, 15500, 15500, 16800], "concluded_range": [15000, 15500], "rationale": "Pairs 1–3 produce $15,000–$15,500 — tight market support. Pair 4 ($16,800) is a modest outlier; address but do not weight heavily. Reconcile within Pairs 1–3."}, "cnd": {"pair_answers": [12200, 12200, 12300], "concluded_range": [12200, 12300], "rationale": "Three pairs produce $12,200, $12,200, and $12,300 — an exceptionally tight $100 spread, providing unusually strong market support."}, "date": {"pair_answers": [0.363, 0.324, 0.351], "concluded_range": [0.32, 0.37], "rationale": "Three resale pairs produce 0.36%, 0.32%, and 0.35%/mo. Tight market support for monthly appreciation rate."}}, "cost": {"gla": {"answer": 56.69, "rationale": "$83.00 × (1 − 0.317) = $56.69/SF. Falls above the consistent paired sales range of $48.00–$49.00/SF — a clear ceiling. Weight paired sales; cost confirms the upper bound is not exceeded. In a condemnation hearing, this cost ceiling helps demonstrate that the value conclusion is appropriately conservative."}}}, "step2_reconciliation": {"gla": {"range": [48.0, 49.0], "rationale": "Paired sales support $48.00–$49.00/SF (Pairs 1–3). Pair 4 ($59.00/SF) excluded with litigation-quality documented reasoning. Cost support of $56.69/SF acts as a clear ceiling, reinforcing that the conclusion is appropriately conservative and defensible. Reconcile near $48.50/SF, weighting paired sales."}, "loc": {"range": [15000, 15500], "rationale": "Paired sales support $15,000–$15,500 (Pairs 1–3). Pair 4 ($16,800) addressed but not weighted. No cost method applicable. Reconcile near the midpoint at approximately $15,250."}, "cnd": {"range": [12200, 12300], "rationale": "Three pairs produce $100 spread — exceptionally tight market support. No cost method applicable. Reconcile near $12,250."}, "date": {"range": [0.33, 0.36], "rationale": "Paired sales support 0.32–0.36%/mo. No cost method applicable. Reconcile near 0.345%/mo."}}, "step3_adjustments": {"C1": {"gla": {"direction": "negative", "amount_per_unit": -48.5, "units": 150, "computed_amount": -7275, "method": "Paired Sales Analysis", "rationale": "Comp 1 is 150 SF larger than the subject (superior). At reconciled $48.50/SF (drawn from Pairs 1–3; Pair 4 outlier excluded with documented reasoning), the GLA adjustment is −$7,275. Cost support of $56.69/SF acts as a clear ceiling, confirming the conclusion is well-bounded for litigation defense."}, "loc": {"direction": "negative", "amount": -15250, "method": "Location Paired Sales Analysis", "rationale": "Comp 1 is in an amenitied/gated community (superior to the subject''s standard location). The location premium derived from three Pairs 1–3 is approximately $15,250 (midpoint of the $15,000–$15,500 range). No cost method applicable for location."}}, "C2": {"cnd": {"direction": "positive", "amount": 12250, "method": "Paired Sales Analysis", "rationale": "Comp 2 is in average condition versus the subject''s good condition (inferior). The condition increment from three exceptionally tight pairs ($12,200–$12,300) is approximately $12,250. No cost method applicable; market reaction governs."}}, "C3": {"gla": {"direction": "positive", "amount_per_unit": 48.5, "units": 150, "computed_amount": 7275, "method": "Paired Sales Analysis", "rationale": "Comp 3 is 150 SF smaller than the subject (inferior). At reconciled $48.50/SF, the GLA adjustment is +$7,275 — opposing direction from Comp 1''s GLA adjustment, demonstrating that GLA must be applied based on each comp''s relationship to the subject."}, "loc": {"direction": "negative", "amount": -15250, "method": "Location Paired Sales Analysis", "rationale": "Comp 3 is in an amenitied/gated community (superior). Same location premium as applied to Comp 1: approximately $15,250 negative. Comp 3 has opposing GLA (positive) and Location (negative) adjustments — both must be applied independently, and the net vs. gross distinction will be addressed in weighting."}, "date": {"direction": "positive", "amount": 14004, "method": "Market Conditions (Resale Pairs)", "rationale": "Comp 3 sold 11 months ago in an appreciating market (inferior date). At reconciled 0.345%/mo: $369,000 × 11 × 0.345 ÷ 100 = $14,004. Three resale pairs support this rate, bringing Comp 3 in line with current market values for the just compensation determination."}}}, "step4_adjusted_prices": {"C1": {"unadjusted": 388000, "adjusted": 365475}, "C2": {"unadjusted": 357000, "adjusted": 369250}, "C3": {"unadjusted": 369000, "adjusted": 375029}}, "step4_reconciliation_narrative": "Adjusted prices cluster in a tight band of approximately $365,475–$375,029 — a spread of less than $10,000 across three comparables and six total adjustments. The just compensation opinion is well-supported in the $367,000–$373,000 range. Comp 2 — requiring only a single, exceptionally tight-bracketed condition adjustment — is given primary weight. Comp 1 (two same-direction adjustments) receives secondary weight. Comp 3, while analytically sound, carries a substantial gross adjustment burden (three adjustments including opposing-direction GLA and Location) and is given the lowest weight. The advanced-level eminent domain teaching points are: (1) the GLA Pair 4 outlier ($59.00/SF) must be excluded with litigation-quality documented reasoning — the SCDOT appraiser may cite it to argue for a higher value if the exclusion is not transparently supported; (2) three of four adjustment types lack cost support and rely entirely on paired sales evidence; (3) Comp 3''s opposing-direction GLA and Location adjustments demonstrate that net and gross adjustments tell different stories; and (4) just compensation is fair market value as of the date of taking — not value to the owner, not replacement cost. Cost support for GLA ($56.69/SF) establishes a clear ceiling well above the $48–$49/SF paired sales conclusion, reinforcing that the conclusion is appropriately conservative and defensible at a Daubert-style hearing.", "tolerance_note": "Student answers are accepted within ±5% of model derived values for paired-sales calculations and within the indicated reconciliation range. Step 3 adjustments accepted within ±13% of the computed amount for GLA, ±12% for fixed-amount features, and ±16% for market conditions."}'::jsonb
FROM scenarios s
JOIN scenario_categories sc ON sc.id = s.category_id
JOIN module_sections ms ON ms.id = sc.section_id
JOIN section_fields f ON f.section_id = ms.id AND f.field_key = 'adjustment_grid'
WHERE sc.code = 'M2-S4-C5'
  AND s.order_index = 3;

-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
-- Scenario: 218 Lakeview Court — Lake Access Community Appraisal
-- Category M2-S4-C6 #1 · difficulty 'basic'
-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
INSERT INTO scenarios
  (category_id, order_index, difficulty, title, scenario_text)
SELECT id, 1,
  'basic',
  '218 Lakeview Court — Lake Access Community Appraisal',
  'You are appraising a home at 218 Lakeview Court, Seneca SC for a purchase loan, on referral from Mountain Lakes Mortgage. Contract price is $342,000. The property includes deeded community lake access to Lake Keowee — a shared dock and boat launch, not direct waterfront frontage. Lake access markets are stratified into distinct tiers: direct lakefront, deeded community access, and no access. These tiers are not interchangeable — using a direct lakefront comparable to support a deeded-access appraisal without adjustment would overstate value; using a non-access comparable without adjustment would understate it. Comparable selection is the first critical step in a lake appraisal.

The subject is a 1,920 SF home built in 2012 with three bedrooms, two full bathrooms, and a 2-car garage, in good condition. Three closed sales are provided. Comps 1 and 2 share the subject''s deeded community access; Comp 3 has no lake access and requires a lake access adjustment. The lake access adjustment has no applicable cost method — you cannot build a lake — and must be derived entirely from paired market evidence within the Lake Keowee deeded-access submarket. The cost-vs-market gap on GLA is striking and characteristic of lake-area markets, where land and location premiums dominate total value. Identify the differing features, derive market-supported adjustment values, apply them, and reconcile the adjusted prices into your opinion of market value.'
FROM scenario_categories WHERE code = 'M2-S4-C6';

