ice Diff"], "concluded_label": "Concluded GLA Adjustment", "concluded_helper": "Bracket toward Pairs 1 & 2; Pair 3 outlier excluded with documented reasoning."}, {"kind": "paired_dollar_diff", "feature_key": "solar", "title": "Solar PV Pairs — None vs. Owned", "instruction": "Pairs isolate the solar PV difference. All from confirmed owned-panel properties — leased systems excluded per Fannie Mae SEL-2019-07. Subtract the no-solar sale price from the owned-solar sale price.", "input_label": "Your Price Difference", "input_suffix": "", "rows": [{"label": "1", "cells": ["$330,000", "$342,500"]}, {"label": "2", "cells": ["$336,000", "$348,000"]}], "column_headers": ["Pair", "No Solar Sale", "Owned Solar Sale"], "concluded_label": "Concluded Solar PV Adjustment", "concluded_helper": "Bracket your two results."}, {"kind": "paired_pct_per_month", "feature_key": "date", "title": "Market Conditions — Resale Pair Analysis", "instruction": "The same properties sold twice. For each pair, calculate the monthly appreciation rate using: (Resale − Original) ÷ Original ÷ Months × 100", "input_label": "Your %/Month", "input_suffix": "%/mo", "rows": [{"label": "A", "cells": ["$328,000", "$338,540", "9"]}, {"label": "B", "cells": ["$334,000", "$345,000", "10"]}, {"label": "C", "cells": ["$322,000", "$332,900", "11"]}], "column_headers": ["Property", "Original Sale Price", "Resale Price", "Months"], "concluded_label": "Concluded Monthly Rate", "concluded_helper": "Bracket your three results."}]}, {"key": "cost", "label": "Cost-Based Support", "intro": "Only GLA has an applicable cost method. The GLA cost indication is a high ceiling — and is nearly identical to the Pair 3 outlier ($64.00/SF), supporting the explanation that Pair 3 reflects cost-influenced rather than market-driven pricing. Solar PV and Market Conditions are market-derived only — Fannie Mae SEL-2019-07 explicitly prohibits using depreciated cost as the sole support for solar PV adjustments.", "items": [{"kind": "cost_calc", "feature_key": "gla", "title": "GLA Contributory Value ($/SF)", "fact_rows": [["RCN", "$80.00 / SF"], ["Effective Age", "10 years"], ["Economic Life", "60 years"], ["Depreciation Rate", "10 ÷ 60 = 16.7%"], ["Formula", "$80.00 × (1 − 0.167) = ?"]], "input_suffix": "/SF"}]}], "reconciliation": {"instruction": "Review both method indications and enter your reconciled adjustment for each item. GLA cost is a high ceiling — weight Pairs 1 & 2 strongly. Solar PV and Market Conditions reconcile from paired sales only.", "items": [{"feature_key": "gla", "label": "GLA Adjustment ($/SF)"}, {"feature_key": "solar", "label": "Solar PV Adjustment ($)"}, {"feature_key": "date", "label": "Market Conditions Adjustment (%/mo)"}]}}, "step3": {"instruction": "Apply your reconciled adjustments to each comparable. Use a NEGATIVE value where the comp is superior to the subject, and a POSITIVE value where it is inferior. Comp 1 receives a negative GLA adjustment. Comp 2 has no solar PV while the subject has owned PV (inferior) — positive solar adjustment. Comp 3 sold 9 months ago in an appreciating market (inferior date) — positive market conditions adjustment. Formula for Comp 3: $326,500 × 9 months × your reconciled %/mo ÷ 100. Each rationale should cite the paired sales evidence and confirm ownership status for the solar pairs.", "applicable": {"C1": ["gla"], "C2": ["solar"], "C3": ["date"]}, "method_dropdown": ["Paired Sales Analysis", "Market Conditions (Resale Pairs)", "Cost-Based Support", "Grouped Paired Sales", "Regression Analysis", "Appraiser Judgment / Extraction"], "support_min_chars": 15}, "step4": {"show_net_gross_panel": false}}'::jsonb,
  '{"step1_correct_flags": {"C1": ["gla"], "C2": ["solar"], "C3": ["date"]}, "step1_rationale": "Comp 1 is 150 SF larger than the subject (superior GLA, single negative adjustment). Comp 2 has no solar PV while the subject has an owned 8.2 kW system (inferior, single positive adjustment). Comp 3 sold 9 months ago in an appreciating market (inferior date, single positive adjustment). Bathrooms, bedrooms, garage, year built, and condition are equivalent across all three comparables. The solar pairs used as support are confirmed from owned-panel properties only, per Fannie Mae SEL-2019-07.", "step2_tables": {"paired": {"gla": {"pair_answers": [46.33, 47.33, 64.0], "concluded_range": [46.33, 48.0], "rationale": "Pairs 1 and 2 cluster tightly at $46.33 and $47.33/SF — consistent market evidence. Pair 3 diverges significantly to $64.00/SF and must be excluded with documented reasoning. Notably, the Pair 3 result is nearly identical to the depreciated GLA cost ($66.64/SF), suggesting Pair 3 may reflect cost-influenced pricing rather than typical market behavior — further reason to exclude it. Bracket conclusion toward Pairs 1 & 2."}, "solar": {"pair_answers": [12500, 12000], "concluded_range": [12000, 12500], "rationale": "Two pairs from confirmed owned-panel properties bracket the solar PV premium at $12,000 and $12,500 — consistent market support. Lease-status confirmation is critical per Fannie Mae SEL-2019-07."}, "date": {"pair_answers": [0.357, 0.329, 0.307], "concluded_range": [0.29, 0.37], "rationale": "Three resale pairs produce 0.36%, 0.33%, and 0.31%/mo. Tight market support; bracket toward central tendency near 0.335%/mo."}}, "cost": {"gla": {"answer": 66.64, "rationale": "$80.00 × (1 − 0.167) = $66.64/SF. Significantly above the consistent paired sales range ($46.33–$47.33/SF) — high ceiling. Notably nearly identical to the Pair 3 outlier ($64.00/SF), reinforcing the conclusion that Pair 3 reflects cost-influenced pricing. Weight paired sales (Pairs 1 & 2)."}}}, "step2_reconciliation": {"gla": {"range": [46.0, 48.0], "rationale": "Paired sales support $46.33–$47.33/SF (Pairs 1 & 2). Pair 3 ($64.00/SF) excluded with documented reasoning, supported by its near-alignment with the cost ceiling. Cost support of $66.64/SF acts only as a high ceiling. Reconcile near $47/SF."}, "solar": {"range": [12000, 12500], "rationale": "Paired sales bracket $12,000–$12,500 from confirmed owned-panel properties. No cost method applicable per Fannie Mae SEL-2019-07. Reconcile near $12,250."}, "date": {"range": [0.32, 0.35], "rationale": "Paired sales support 0.31–0.36%/mo. No cost method applicable. Reconcile near 0.335%/mo."}}, "step3_adjustments": {"C1": {"gla": {"direction": "negative", "amount_per_unit": -47.0, "units": 150, "computed_amount": -7050, "method": "Paired Sales Analysis", "rationale": "Comp 1 is 150 SF larger than the subject (superior). At reconciled $47/SF (Pairs 1 & 2; Pair 3 outlier excluded — its near-alignment with the $66.64/SF cost ceiling supports the cost-influenced-pricing explanation), the GLA adjustment is −$7,050. Cost support acts only as a high ceiling."}}, "C2": {"solar": {"direction": "positive", "amount": 12250, "method": "Paired Sales Analysis", "rationale": "Comp 2 has no solar PV while the subject has an owned 8.2 kW system (inferior). The owned-solar premium derived from two paired sales of confirmed owned-panel properties is approximately $12,250 (midpoint of $12,000–$12,500). No cost method applicable per Fannie Mae SEL-2019-07 — depreciated PV equipment cost consistently and significantly overstates market contribution."}}, "C3": {"date": {"direction": "positive", "amount": 9843, "method": "Market Conditions (Resale Pairs)", "rationale": "Comp 3 sold 9 months ago in an appreciating market (inferior date). At reconciled 0.335%/mo: $326,500 × 9 × 0.335 ÷ 100 = $9,843. Three resale pairs support this rate, bringing Comp 3 in line with current market values."}}}, "step4_adjusted_prices": {"C1": {"unadjusted": 356000, "adjusted": 348950}, "C2": {"unadjusted": 341000, "adjusted": 353250}, "C3": {"unadjusted": 326500, "adjusted": 336343}}, "step4_reconciliation_narrative": "Adjusted prices range from approximately $336,343 to $353,250 — a spread of about $17,000 across three comparables and three different adjustment types. The opinion of market value is supported in the $343,000–$352,000 range, comfortably bracketing the $348,000 contract price. Solar PV appraisal is one of the fastest-growing specialty situations in residential practice. The key analytical principle is that ownership status determines methodology: owned systems require paired sales analysis from confirmed owned-panel comparables; leased systems require a negative or zero adjustment reflecting the lease liability. Fannie Mae''s SEL-2019-07 guidance explicitly prohibits using depreciated cost as the sole support for a solar PV adjustment — and the data here illustrates why: the depreciated GLA cost of $66.64/SF is strikingly close to the Pair 3 GLA outlier ($64.00/SF), suggesting that pair may have been influenced by a buyer willing to pay above market for improvement features. Pairs 1 & 2 at $46.33–$47.33/SF, supported by a cost ceiling at $66.64/SF, produce a well-bounded conclusion. The solar paired sales ($12,000–$12,500) are consistent and from confirmed owned-panel properties — the documentation requirement around ownership status is not bureaucratic detail; it is the difference between a defensible adjustment and one that could be challenged at the underwriting desk or in a secondary market review.", "tolerance_note": "Student answers are accepted within ±5% of model derived values for paired-sales calculations and within the indicated reconciliation range. Step 3 adjustments accepted within ±13% of the computed amount for GLA, ±12% for fixed-amount features, and ±16% for market conditions."}'::jsonb
FROM scenarios s
JOIN scenario_categories sc ON sc.id = s.category_id
JOIN module_sections ms ON ms.id = sc.section_id
JOIN section_fields f ON f.section_id = ms.id AND f.field_key = 'adjustment_grid'
WHERE sc.code = 'M2-S4-C6'
  AND s.order_index = 2;

-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
-- Scenario: 5204 Ashbrook Manor Drive — ADU, Pool & Multi-Feature Capstone
-- Category M2-S4-C6 #3 · difficulty 'advanced'
-- ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
INSERT INTO scenarios
  (category_id, order_index, difficulty, title, scenario_text)
SELECT id, 3,
  'advanced',
  '5204 Ashbrook Manor Drive — ADU, Pool & Multi-Feature Capstone',
  'You are appraising a home at 5204 Ashbrook Manor Drive, Greenville SC for a purchase loan, on referral from Highlands Mortgage Group. Contract price is $468,000. This is the Section 4 capstone — the most analytically complex scenario in the section. Five adjustment types are distributed across three comparables, with each comparable requiring exactly two adjustments. Comps 1 and 2 both carry opposing-direction adjustments. A GLA outlier must be identified and excluded. ADU cost support will dramatically exceed market evidence — a critical specialty lesson about how the market discounts secondary units relative to their replacement cost.

The subject is a 2,550 SF home built in 2011 with three full bathrooms, four bedrooms, a 2-car garage, in good condition, in a standard (non-amenitied) subdivision. The property includes a 520 SF detached ADU (guest cottage, confirmed as real property) and an in-ground pool. Three closed sales are provided. They differ from the subject across five adjustment types: GLA, ADU, pool, location, and market conditions. Comp 1 has GLA superior and no ADU (opposing-direction adjustments). Comp 2 has no pool but is in an amenitied/gated community (opposing-direction adjustments). Comp 3 has GLA inferior and sold 10 months ago (both inferior, same direction). The GLA Pair 4 outlier must be excluded — and notably, its result is nearly identical to the GLA cost indication, supporting a cost-influenced-pricing explanation. The ADU adjustment derived from paired sales (~$16,250) is roughly 40% of depreciated replacement cost ($39,520) — a structural characteristic of ADU valuation that reflects financing complexity, management burden, and a narrower buyer pool. Identify the differing features, derive market-supported adjustments, apply them independently, and reconcile into your opinion of market value.'
FROM scenario_categories WHERE code = 'M2-S4-C6';

